
This is a simple Spring boot project build to deploy in Kubernetes cluster using docker images. 

Steps :
1. Build a simple Spring boot maven project
2. Create application .jar file
3. Create a 'Dockerfile' in main application package. 
   The Dockerfile need to have following information :
   FROM <>
   EXPOSE <port>
   COPY <>
   ENTRYPOINT <>
4. Open your terminal, For example in windows open your Powershell and locate to your Dockerfile .. cd .. 
5. Build Docker image 
   docker build -t <dockerimage name> .
   This will create docker image.
6. Validate docker image is created or not. 
   Run command : docker images 
   This will list all the docker images available
7. Tag you docker image correctly
   docker tag springbootk8sdemo <DockerHub Username>/<docker image name>:latest
8. Push the image to Docker Hub
   docker push <DockerHub Username>/<docker image name>:latest

10. (Optional) Run the Docker container locally
   docker run -p <host_port>:<container_port> <dockerimage name>
   This will start your application and map the container port to your local machine.

9. Confirm your Docker Hub
   Visit: https://hub.docker.com/repository/docker/<dockerhub username>/<dockerimage name>
